HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 373
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Pleasant View 6U
All-Stars baseball team, Dixie Youth Baseball
World Series Champions.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially honor and commend those successful
athletic teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, the Pleasant View 6U All-Stars baseball team is one such exemplary group
of young athletes, that won the 2024 Dixie Youth Baseball World Series in Walterboro, South
Carolina, with a record of 7-1; and
WHEREAS, this tremendous team compiled a combined record of 26-4 on the season,
winning the district tournament in four straight games to advance to the state tournament in
Harriman where the team claimed the first state title in the history of Pleasant View; and
WHEREAS, proudly representing the State of Tennessee at the national tournament, the
Pleasant View 6U All-Stars won the team skills competition to start the week and rolled through
their opponents to claim the crown of national champion, outscoring their foes 441-190 for the
season; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Pleasant View 6U All-Stars baseball team are
Demarcus Simmons, Avery Merritt, Colin Garrison, Knox Perryman, Lincoln Carter, Beckham
James, Owen Head, Jake Walker, Cortland Whittemore, Carson Sims, K.J. Blackwell, and Lane
Davis; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Pleasant View 6U All-Stars baseball team undoubtedly
benefited from the vast knowledge and stalwart leadership of a committed group of coaches,
including E.J. Sims, Eric Whittemore, Adam Carter, and Eric Sims; and
